    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.10.34"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">34</fw>
                
                <fw type="authorial">
                    THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA 
                    LINCOLN, NEBRASKA 68508 
                    
                    OFFICE OF THE DIRECTOR 
                    UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA PRESS
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 28, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John G. Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68505</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your broadcast on Channel 7 last nigth was truly magnificient.</p> 
                <p>I was especially emotionally inspired listening to your description of the agony of Crazy Horse. You are a wonderful man Dr. Neihardt and I am so pleased that our country now has a star in the firmament of American literature who grows in brilliance each passing day.</p> 
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>Cordially,</salute>
                    <salute>UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA PRESS</salute>
                    <signed>Bruce</signed> 
                    <signed>Bruce H. Nicoll</signed> 
                    <signed>Director</signed> 
                    
                    
                    <note>BHN:ks</note> 
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
